docs.lead_paragraph: PRINCETON, N.J., Oct. 10. -- The National Alumni Association of Princeton University will meet in Detroit on Friday and Saturday Oct. 28 and 29, it was announced here today by Thurston J. Davies, Secretary of the association. The Michigan-Princeton football game at Ann Arbor, Mich., will be the main feature of Saturday's program.

docs.lead_paragraph: Now that we are still stumbling about in the depression the authors of "Men Must Fight," which was acted at the Lyceum last evening, remind us that we are not yet safely out of war. Reginald Lawrence and S.K. Lauren have set their play forward to 1940 when the United States apparently goes to war with most of South America for the manliest of reasons.

docs.lead_paragraph: CHARLESTON, S.C., Oct. ,20. -- An imposing monument in granite and bronze, sculptured by Sermon A. MacNeil, and built with a bequest of $100,000 left by the Late Andrew B. Murray, Charleston philanthropist, as a memorial to the Confederate defenders of Fort Sumter, was dedicated on the battery this afternoon.
